    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Description of Jehoshaphat's power. - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 17:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". And Jehoshaphat became ever greater, sc. in power. The partic. הולך expresses the continuous advance in greatness, cf. Ew. 280, b, as the infin. absol. does elsewhere, e.g., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 8:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". למעלה עד as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 16:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". - He built castles in Judah. בּירניּות, only here and in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 27:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", from בּירנית, derivative formed from בּירה by the Syriac termination נית-, fem. of  ן-: castle, fortress. On מסכּנות ערי cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
